TITLE: At 82, Glenda Jackson Commands the Most Powerful Role in Theater
SUMMARY: “King Lear” has long been the crowning performance for actors who know how to dominate a stage. As a longstanding member of Parliament, Jackson has unique insight into authority.

TITLE: Prime Power: How Amazon Squeezes the Businesses Behind Its Store
SUMMARY: Twenty years ago, Amazon opened its storefront to anyone who wanted to sell something. Then it began demanding more out of them.
